BUNDA district in Mara region has received a donation of 31 street signboards from Grumeti Fund to help the ongoing national residential addresses and postcode exercise in the area. “I thank the Grumeti Fund for supporting this national exercise of residential addresses in our district “, Bunda District Commissioner (DC) Mr Joshua Nassari said during the handing over of the street signboards event held at his office on Thursday. According to Mr Nassari implementation of the national addresses and postcode exercise was doing well in the district. Therefore, he said, the street signboards donated by Grumeti will have a significant contribution to speed up the exercise in the area. “Already, we are doing very well and actually according to reports from the ministry Bunda district is leading in terms of data collection among other areas in our region of Mara “, Mr Nassari said. Grumeti Fund is a non-profit making organization that supports conservation and community development activities in Western Serengeti. Mr Nassari described Grumeti Fund as one of the key conservation partners, supporting and protecting the Serengeti ecosystem for the present and future generations. “On behalf of the government I thank you (Grumeti ) and we are together in wildlife conservation”, he said. Grumeti Fund Community Relationships Manager, Mr David Mwakipesile said the donation of the signboards was meant to support the government’s ongoing residential addresses and postcode exercise. “On behalf of my General Manager at Grumeti Fund I am happy to hand over these signboards to support the residential addresses exercise going on in our country “, Mr Mwakipesile said.